From: GoByte Core Developers <dev@gobyte.network>
Subject: [PATCH] qt 5.9.6: add missing <limits> include for GCC 13/libstdc++13

GCC 13's libstdc++ (GCC PR 108527) removed many historically-transitive
standard-header inclusions. Qt 5.9.6's QStaticByteArrayMatcherBase::generate()
uses std::numeric_limits<uchar> but relies on it arriving transitively;
that chain is now broken.

The fix is the minimal standard-conformant solution: add the explicit
#include <limits> to qbytearraymatcher.h. No Qt logic is altered;
compiled output is functionally identical to prior GCC versions.

Observed: Ubuntu 24.04 / GCC 13.x / x86_64-pc-linux-gnu
          (GitHub Actions ubuntu-latest, 2026-Q1)
---

--- a/qtbase/src/corelib/tools/qbytearraymatcher.h
+++ b/qtbase/src/corelib/tools/qbytearraymatcher.h
@@ -41,6 +41,7 @@
 #define QBYTEARRAYMATCHER_H

 #include <QtCore/qbytearray.h>
+#include <limits>

 QT_BEGIN_NAMESPACE
